Root Cause
The application treated an unpredictable identifier as if it were an authorization mechanism.

The GUID only made guessing more difficult.

It did not verify ownership of the requested resource.

Impact
Successful exploitation may expose:

API Keys
Personal information
Customer accounts
Financial records
Medical data
Private documents
Internal resources
If sensitive operations are available, attackers may also modify or delete another user's data.

Prevention
Never rely on unpredictable IDs for security.
Perform server-side authorization checks on every request.
Verify resource ownership before returning data.
Use authenticated session information whenever possible.
Treat GUIDs only as identifiers, not as access control.
